{
  "text": "Although the feature ownership matrices are generated independent of each other from the standard IBP (Z (a) ϳ IBP(␣)), the feature images are generated from a common source Y (0) , according to the rules of the CRP (Y (a) |Y (0) ϳ CRP(␤)). The new dishes in Y (0) are generated from the feature image prior, which has been an independent Bernoulli prior in this article. Figure 17 illustrates how this model infers features after observing the first two objects of each category that have been categorized according to the horizontal scheme of [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "5905431"
